<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,437]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,201,159,185]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[209,449,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott ex Pohl" authorityYear="1831" box="[238,449,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thapsoidea">Lobelia thapsoidea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was distinguished by Schott and validly published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, J. B. E." bookContentInfo="152 pp." box="[1049,1185,158,184]" firstAuthor="Pohl" journalOrPublisher="Wien" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" refId="ref7738" refString="Pohl, J. B. E. (1831) Plantarum Brasiliae Icones et Descriptiones, vol. 2. Wien, 152 pp." title="Plantarum Brasiliae Icones et Descriptiones, vol. 2" type="book" year="1831">Pohl (1831)</bibRefCitation>
. The species protologue provides a diagnosis, locality indication (“ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Habitat circa 
<collectingRegion box="[766,932,194,220]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, Lecta a Dno. Schott, a me visa ad Ouro Fino, Capitaniae Goyaz
</emphasis>
”), and detailed description. Our herbarium search led to the collection 
<emphasis box="[1154,1289,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Schott 5372</emphasis>
, housed at W. A label matching the description in the protologue was attached to the sheet number W0058406, but contained only leaves. The sheet number W0058405, with a label identical to that of the sheet W0058406, had an inflorescence and only one leaf, which was too large to have been removed from the apex of the stem. These plant fragments are clearly part of a single specimen that was mounted on two sheets. According to Art. 8.2 of ICN (
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill, J." box="[1136,1298,374,400]" firstAuthor="McNeill" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" pagination="1112 - 1113" part="63" refId="ref7546" refString="McNeill, J. (2014) Holotype specimens and type citations: General issues. Taxon 63: 1112 - 1113. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 635.7" title="Holotype specimens and type citations: General issues" type="journal article" year="2014">McNeill 2014</bibRefCitation>
), these sheets represent a single specimen and are here interpreted as the 
<typeStatus box="[795,897,410,436]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
